<div class="ultimate-harvester-form">
  <div class="ultimate-harvester-section">
    <p><strong>{{foragerName}}</strong> prepares to forage in the <strong>{{environment}}</strong></p>
  </div>

  <div class="ultimate-harvester-section">
    <div class="ultimate-harvester-section-header">
      <span>{{localize "MHARVEST.Dialog.HowManyHours"}}</span>
    </div>
    <input type="number" name="hours" value="2" min="1" max="8" step="1" />
    <p class="ultimate-harvester-note"><i class="fas fa-clock ultimate-harvester-icon--time"></i> Every 2 hours after the first reduces the DC by 1</p>
  </div>

  <div class="ultimate-harvester-section">
    <div class="ultimate-harvester-section-header">
      <span>Difficulty Tiers</span>
    </div>
    <p class="ultimate-harvester-note">
      Basic: DC {{tier1DC}} &nbsp;|&nbsp;
      Successful: DC {{tier2DC}} &nbsp;|&nbsp;
      Bountiful: DC {{tier3DC}} &nbsp;|&nbsp;
      Nat 19+: Rare find
    </p>
  </div>

  <details>
    <summary class="ultimate-harvester-details-toggle">How does foraging work?</summary>
    <ul class="ultimate-harvester-details-list">
      <li>Roll your skill check &mdash; the highest tier you meet determines what you can find</li>
      <li>You'll always find food and water first, with a chance at rarer materials</li>
      <li>Better rolls improve the quality and quantity of your finds</li>
      <li>Every 2 extra hours reduces the DC by 1 (more time = easier to find something)</li>
      <li>A natural 19 or 20 grants a bonus rare item</li>
      <li>One foraging session per long rest</li>
      <li>Foraging characters cannot contribute to passive Perception</li>
    </ul>
  </details>
</div>
